        "verdict": "no evidence",
        "rationale": "RA's covalent target is activated C3b (Sahu 1999 mechanism: covalent attachment to activated C3b). The chemistry is electrophilic addition to nucleophilic acceptor sites on the deposited C3b. DAF SCR1-4 binds C3b via reversible CCP-domain protein-protein interaction; there is no published report of RA inactivating any CCP/SCR domain protein."
